## Prerequisites ##

In order to deploy Pivotal Cloud Foundry on vSphere, you must have a dedicated vSphere account/project/thing that meets the following requirements.

!!!All this stuff is from openstack and needs to be replaced!!!

* Credentials...

	* Auth URL
	* API key
	* Username
	* Project name
	* Region
	* SSL certificate for your wildcard domain (see below).

* The following must be enabled for the tenant:

!!!All this stuff is from openstack and needs to be replaced!!!

	* The ability to allocate floating IPs.
	* The ability for VMs inside a tenant to send messages via the floating IP.
	* Permissions for VMs to boot directly from image.
  * One wildcard DNS domain. Pivotal recommends using two wildcard domains if system and apps need to be separated.
	

* Your vSphere tenant must have the following resources before you install Pivotal Cloud Foundry:
	
!!!All this stuff is from openstack and needs to be replaced!!!

	* 70 GB of RAM
	* 22 available instances
	* 16 small VMs (1 vCPU, 1024 MB of RAM, 10 GB of root disk)
	* 3 large VMs (4 vCPU, 16384 MB of RAM, 10 GB root disk)
	* 32 vCPUs
	* 1 TB of storage
	* Neutron networking with floating IP support


* Miscellaneous:

	* Pivotal recommends granting complete access to the vSphere logs to the operator managing the installation process.
	* Your vSphere environment should be thoroughly tested and considered stable before deploying PCF.
	